# Weather Information Visualization (ES6)

This project visualizes weather data using modern JavaScript (ES6). It is designed to help you learn about API integration, data visualization, and responsive UI design.

## Features
- Fetches real-time weather data from an API
- Visualizes temperature, humidity, and conditions
- Responsive and interactive charts
- Clean, user-friendly interface

## Folder Structure
- `images/`: Weather icons and backgrounds
- `public/`: HTML, CSS, and JS files for the app

## How to Use
1. Open the main HTML file in your browser.
2. Enter a city or location to view weather data.
3. Explore the code to see how ES6 features are used.

## Learning Outcomes
- Work with APIs and asynchronous JavaScript
- Visualize data with charts and graphics
- Build interactive, modern web apps

